headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 24 points and the Dallas Mavericks led by a NBA-record 50 points at halftime in a 124-73 rout of the Los Angeles Clippers on Sunday to earn their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs destroy Clippers 124-73 to earn 1st win of season

headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward had 28 points, seven assists and six rebounds, and the Charlotte Hornets handed the Brooklyn Nets their first loss of the season, 106-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayward, Hornets hand Nets first loss of season, 106-104

headlines.description: — Markelle Fultz and Terrence Ross each scored 26 points as the Orlando Magic mounted a big fourth quarter comeback and beat the Washington Wizards 120-113 on Sunday night to start a season 3-0 for the first time since 2009-10.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic defeat Wizards 120-113 as Westbrook sits

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram had 28 points and 11 rebounds and the New Orleans Pelicans held on for a 98-95 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Ingram scores 28 points, Pelicans beat Spurs 98-95

headlines.description: — Andre Drummond scored 24 points, grabbed 14 rebounds and made three steals as the Cleveland Cavaliers won their third straight game to start the season, 118-94 over the Philadelphia 76ers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs win 3rd straight to open season, rout 76ers 118-94

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Tom Thibodeau's first victory as Knicks coach came surprisingly easy against a top opponent, as New York routed the Milwaukee Bucks 130-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rout Bucks 130-110 for first victory under Thibodeau

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored on a layup with 8.4 seconds left and finished with his 100th career double-double, helping the Indiana Pacers get past Boston 108-107 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis hits late basket, sends Pacers past Celtics 108-107

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Damion Lee hit a 3-pointer with 1.7 seconds remaining and Stephen Curry scored 36 points, sending the Golden State Warriors to a 129-128 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Sunday night for their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lee's late 3 lifts Warriors over winless Bulls 129-128

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 22 points, Cameron Johnson had 21 in 21 minutes and the Phoenix Suns pulled away with two second-half runs top beat the Sacramento Kings 116-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns use 2 big 2nd-half runs to beat Kings 116-100

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 20 points in the first half while starting in Anthony Davis' place, and LeBron James added 18 points in the Los Angeles Lakers' 127-91 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma leads AD-less Lakers' 127-91 thrashing of Timberwolves
